309
00:24:34,155 --> 00:24:36,111
You came to see a race today.

310
00:24:36,195 --> 00:24:38,186
To see someone win.

311
00:24:38,595 --> 00:24:40,586
It happened to be me.

312
00:24:41,315 --> 00:24:44,148
But I want you to do more
than just watch a race.

313
00:24:44,915 --> 00:24:46,906
I want you to take part in it.

314
00:24:47,995 --> 00:24:51,590
I want to compare faith to running in a race.

315
00:24:52,955 --> 00:24:54,946
It's hard.

316
00:24:55,035 --> 00:24:57,265
It requires concentration of will.

317
00:24:57,835 --> 00:24:59,826
Energy of soul.

318
00:25:01,555 --> 00:25:03,432
You experience elation...

319
00:25:03,515 --> 00:25:05,506
...when the winner breaks the tape...

320
00:25:06,435 --> 00:25:08,665
...especially if you've got a bet on it.

321
00:25:09,475 --> 00:25:11,466
But how long does that last?

322
00:25:12,075 --> 00:25:14,509
You go home. Maybe your dinner's burnt.

323
00:25:15,595 --> 00:25:17,904
Maybe you haven't got ajob.

324
00:25:19,115 --> 00:25:21,106
So who am I to say believe...

325
00:25:21,555 --> 00:25:24,388
...have faith, in the face of life's realities?

326
00:25:26,155 --> 00:25:29,067
I would like to give you
something more permanent...

327
00:25:29,155 --> 00:25:31,146
...but I can only point the way.

328
00:25:31,715 --> 00:25:34,104
I have no formula for winning the race.

329
00:25:34,555 --> 00:25:36,546
Everyone runs in her own way...

330
00:25:36,635 --> 00:25:38,626
...or his own way.

331
00:25:38,715 --> 00:25:42,503
And where does the power come from
to see the race to its end?

332
00:25:44,435 --> 00:25:46,426
From within.

333
00:25:47,155 --> 00:25:49,146
Jesus said...

334
00:25:49,235 --> 00:25:52,750
..."Behold, the kingdom of God is within you."

335
00:25:55,035 --> 00:25:58,550
"If with all your hearts ye truly seek me...

336
00:25:58,635 --> 00:26:00,785
...ye shall ever surely find me."

337
00:26:01,275 --> 00:26:03,470
If you commit yourself...

338
00:26:03,555 --> 00:26:05,546
...to the love of Christ...

339
00:26:06,595 --> 00:26:09,667
...then <i>that</i> is how you run a straight race.

340
00:26:16,755 --> 00:26:18,950
Cheers. Thanks for coming.

341
00:26:31,555 --> 00:26:33,546
It's an ache.

342
00:26:34,835 --> 00:26:36,826
A helplessness.

343
00:26:38,635 --> 00:26:40,626
And an anger.

344
00:26:44,435 --> 00:26:46,426
One feels humiliated.

345
00:26:51,955 --> 00:26:55,994
Sometimes I say to myself,
"Steady on, you're imagining all this."

346
00:26:56,755 --> 00:26:58,746
Then I catch that look again.

347
00:26:59,675 --> 00:27:01,666
Catch it on the edge of a remark.

348
00:27:02,475 --> 00:27:04,864
Feel a cold reluctance in a handshake.

349
00:27:10,915 --> 00:27:12,906
That's my father.

350
00:27:12,995 --> 00:27:14,986
A Lithuanian Jew.

351
00:27:15,475 --> 00:27:17,466
He <i>is</i> alien.

352
00:27:17,555 --> 00:27:20,513
- He's as foreign as a frankfurter.
- A kosher one at that!

353
00:27:26,435 --> 00:27:28,426
I love and admire him.

354
00:27:29,715 --> 00:27:31,706
He worships this country.

355
00:27:31,795 --> 00:27:33,990
From nothing, he built what he believed...

356
00:27:34,075 --> 00:27:36,589
...was enough to make
true Englishmen of his sons.

357
00:27:37,555 --> 00:27:39,546
My brother's a doctor.

358
00:27:43,875 --> 00:27:45,866
A leader in his field.

359
00:27:46,755 --> 00:27:50,464
- Which one is he?
- That's me with the curis, on his back.

360
00:27:54,995 --> 00:27:56,986
He wanted for nothing.

361
00:27:59,275 --> 00:28:01,186
And here am I.

362
00:28:01,275 --> 00:28:04,551
<i>Setting up shop</i>
<i>in the finest university in the land.</i>

363
00:28:19,795 --> 00:28:21,786
But the old man forgot one thing.

364
00:28:22,555 --> 00:28:24,546
This England of his is Christian...

365
00:28:24,635 --> 00:28:26,626
...and Anglo-Saxon.

366
00:28:27,155 --> 00:28:29,225
And so are her corridors of power.

367
00:28:30,755 --> 00:28:34,464
And those who stalk them
guard them with jealousy and venom.

368
00:28:35,475 --> 00:28:38,706
You're right to study law.
You're quite an advocate.

369
00:28:38,795 --> 00:28:42,231
A rare ethnic advantage.
It's called the gift of the gab.

370
00:28:48,755 --> 00:28:51,315
So what now? Grin and bear it?

371
00:28:51,395 --> 00:28:53,306
No, Aubrey.

372
00:28:53,395 --> 00:28:56,034
I'm going to take them on. All of them.

373
00:28:56,595 --> 00:28:58,586
One by one.

374
00:28:58,955 --> 00:29:00,946
And run them off their feet.

